This paper deals with neural network compression and acceleration, which are topics commonly studied in the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The paper specifically focuses on convolutional neural networks, which are widely used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the functionality of filters in the neural network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a method for customizing neural networks, which could be relevant to the neural engineering (cs.NE) community. Finally, the paper involves visualizing the filters' functionality, which could be relevant to the natural language processing (cs.CL) community.
